The Telegraph - Calcutta : Nation

 Domestics abuse

 New Delhi, April 10: Domestic workers form the biggest component 23 per cent of children engaged in work and face the worst forms of sexual abuse, a study on child abuse by the Centre has shown.

 Nearly 62 per cent children working as domestic help have faced sexual abuse as compared to 54 per cent living on streets, it says. 




